  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is the best app to make anonymous call online?",
  "response": "When seeking to make anonymous calls online, it's essential to prioritize both privacy and security while ensuring that your actions comply with local laws and regulations. Several apps specialize in providing anonymity by offering disposable or secondary phone numbers. Here are some of the best options available:\n\n1. **Burner**\n   - **Features:** Provides temporary phone numbers for calling and texting. Ideal for maintaining privacy in various situations such as online transactions, dating, or business.\n   - **Platforms:** iOS and Android.\n   - **Pros:** Easy to set up, reliable service, various pricing plans.\n   - **Cons:** Costs can add up with prolonged use.\n\n2. **Hushed**\n   - **Features:** Offers disposable phone numbers with the ability to make calls, send texts, and even use voicemail. Suitable for both personal and business purposes.\n   - **Platforms:** iOS and Android.\n   - **Pros:** Long battery life, multiple number options, flexible subscription plans.\n   - **Cons:** Limited features in the free version.\n\n3. **Google Voice**\n   - **Features:** Provides a free phone number for calls, texts, and voicemail. Integrates seamlessly with other Google services, enhancing usability.\n   - **Platforms:** iOS, Android, and web.\n   - **Pros:** Free to use (with a Google account), reliable call quality, integration with Google ecosystem.\n   - **Cons:** Requires a Google account, limited anonymity compared to disposable number apps.\n\n4. **TextNow**\n   - **Features:** Offers free and premium phone numbers for calling and texting. Includes features like voicemail, call forwarding, and conference calling.\n   - **Platforms:** iOS, Android, and web.\n   - **Pros:** Free basic services, user-friendly interface, international calling options.\n   - **Cons:** Ads in the free version can be intrusive, limited anonymity features.\n\n5. **Signal**\n   - **Features:** While primarily a secure messaging app with end-to-end encryption, Signal also supports encrypted voice and video calls.\n   - **Platforms:** iOS, Android, and desktop.\n   - **Pros:** High level of security and privacy, open-source, no ads or trackers.\n   - **Cons:** Requires a phone number for registration, not specifically designed for anonymity.\n\n6. **Skype with Skype Number**\n   - **Features:** Allows you to purchase a Skype Number that can be used to make and receive calls without revealing your personal number.\n   - **Platforms:** iOS, Android, Windows, macOS, and web.\n   - **Pros:** Well-established service, integrates with Microsoft products, reliable call quality.\n   - **Cons:** Paid service, may not be as anonymous as disposable number apps.\n\n### **Important Considerations**\n\n- **Legal and Ethical Use:** Always use these apps responsibly. Making anonymous calls for harassment, fraud, or other illegal activities is prohibited and punishable by law.\n  \n- **Privacy Policies:** Review the privacy policies of any app you choose to understand how your data is handled and protected.\n\n- **Cost:** While some apps offer free services, they often come with limitations or ads. Premium features typically require a subscription or one-time payment.\n\n- **Reliability:** Ensure the app you choose has good call quality and reliable service to meet your needs effectively.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nFor the best balance of anonymity, features, and ease of use, **Burner** and **Hushed** are often highly recommended for making anonymous calls online. They specialize in providing disposable phone numbers that help protect your personal information. However, if you\u2019re looking for a free and versatile option, **Google Voice** and **TextNow** are also excellent choices, albeit with some limitations regarding anonymity.\n\nAlways ensure that your use of these services aligns with legal guidelines and respects the privacy and rights of others.",
